Exercise 1: Display and Joystick


Included Files:
	-joy_cursor.cpp
	-Makefile
	-README

Accessories:
	-Arduino mega board
	-breadboard jumper wire (5 pcs)
	-breadboard
	-lcd display
	-joystick

Wiring Instructions:
	-Arduino analog pin A8 <--> joystick pin VRx
	-Arduino analog pin A9 <--> joystick pin VRy
	-Arduino digital pin 53 <--> joystick pin SW
	-Arduino ground <--> joystick ground
	-Arduino 5V <--> joystick +5V

Running Instructions:
	-build circuit and connect Arduino to VMware
	-use terminal to navigate to the folder that contains the included files
	-use command 'make upload' to run joy_cursor.cpp on the Arduino and wait for the map to load.
	-The red cursor in the middle of the display will now move in the direction the joystick is pushed.
		The cursor will move faster the further the joystick is pushed in a given direction.
		The cursor is not able to leave the screen or enter the black area of the screen.